{"title":"(21) implementacion-amb-sysmayal2 - Raven","url":"https://erp.sysmayal2.cloud/raven/AMB-Wellness/AMB-Wellness-implementacion-amb-sysmayal2","summary":"This is a technical support channel discussing bug fixes for the Raven AI Agent system integrated with ERPNext. The conversation focuses on fixing invoice creation issues for Mexican CFDI (Comprobante Fiscal Digital por Internet) compliance. The main bugs discussed were: (1) Preview returning raw boolean `True` instead of formatted message, and (2) `mode_of_payment` MandatoryError blocking Sales Invoice creation. Multiple rounds of testing and fixes were performed, with the development team identifying root causes in different files (sales.py vs workflows.py vs command_router.py). The final solution involved removing duplicate invoice command routing in command_router.py so commands fall through to the proper sales.py handler with all 6 CFDI features. All tests passed successfully with Sales Invoice ACC-SINV-2026-00009 created with all required CFDI fields including mode_of_payment, mx_payment_option, mx_cfdi_use, conversion_rate (Banxico FIX), debit_to, and mx_product_service_key.","key_points":["Bug Report: Preview command '@ai invoice from SO-00754-Calipso s.r.l' returned boolean 'True' instead of formatted preview message","Bug Report: Execute command '@ai !invoice from SO-00754-Calipso s.r.l' failed with MandatoryError: mode_of_payment","Root Cause 1: Preview path returned raw boolean instead of formatted text - fixed in commit e76cec9","Root Cause 2: mode_of_payment was never set in workflows.py lines 308-314 despite mx_payment_option and mx_cfdi_use being set","Initial wrong fix: Commit 9405165 fixed sales.py but command was routed to workflows.py instead (command_router.py line 138)","The invoice command was intercepted by command_router.py before reaching sales.py fallback handler","Fix commit d82eb1d: Added mode_of_payment to workflows.py create_invoice_from_sales_order()","Fix commit 1ebd6f5: Removed duplicate invoice path in command_router.py lines 132-139","Final solution: Invoice commands now route to sales.py which has all 6 CFDI features","Test passed: Sales Invoice ACC-SINV-2026-00009 created successfully with all CFDI fields","CFDI fields now properly set: Wire Transfer (mode_of_payment), PPD (mx_payment_option), G01 (mx_cfdi_use)","Additional fields working: Banxico FIX rate 17.7962, CALIPSO debit_to sub-account 1105.2.85, mx_product_service_key 31151517","Pipeline QTN-0754 completed: 100% Delivered + 100% Billed","Next pipelines to process: QTN 0755 (CHARKIT), 0756 (Barentz Italia), 0757 (ALBAFLOR), 0758 (ALPHATECH)"],"relevant_links":["https://erp.sysmayal2.cloud/app/sales-invoice/ACC-SINV-2026-00009"],"file_name":"raven_implementacion_amb_sysmayal2_bug_fixes.json"}
